<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1472,1571]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1472,1498]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Arms 7–14. Papulae absent. Abactinal disk plates with short spinelets. As with all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1875" box="[1246,1378,1472,1498]" class="Asteroidea" family="Brisingidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Brisingida" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Brisingidae</taxonomicName>
, arm plates arranged in costae or ribs along arms, separated by thick skin. Adambulacral plates form adoral carina also referred to as “united interradially by syzygy.” Gonads serial.
</paragraph>
